Subject: bnx2fc: Support max IO size to 512KB
Git-commit: Pending
Patch-mainline: Submitted 22 Dec 2012 linux-scsi@vger.kernel.org
References: FATE#313818,bnc#790595

Increase max_sectors from 512 to 1024 in order to support max IO size of 512KB.

Signed-off-by: Bhanu Prakash Gollapudi <bprakash@broadcom.com>
Acked-by: Michael Chan <mchan@broadcom.com>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/scsi/bnx2fc/bnx2fc_fcoe.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/bnx2fc/bnx2fc_fcoe.c b/drivers/scsi/bnx2fc/bnx2fc_fcoe.c
index beb2478..f7da548 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/bnx2fc/bnx2fc_fcoe.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/bnx2fc/bnx2fc_fcoe.c
@@ -2624,7 +2624,7 @@ static struct scsi_host_template bnx2fc_shost_template = {
 	.can_queue		= BNX2FC_CAN_QUEUE,
 	.use_clustering		= ENABLE_CLUSTERING,
 	.sg_tablesize		= BNX2FC_MAX_BDS_PER_CMD,
-	.max_sectors		= 512,
+	.max_sectors		= 1024,
 };
 
 static struct libfc_function_template bnx2fc_libfc_fcn_templ = {
